          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-08 17:32:59.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 mdt: fix ACTIVE_WRITER lock cancellation",
        "message": "LU-0000 mdt: fix ACTIVE_WRITER lock cancellation\n\nACTIVE_WRITER locks created for immediate mirror files were\nnot sending cancellation RPCs to the server when cancelled\non the client side. This caused the server-side active\nwriter count to remain elevated and not get decremented to 0.\n\nThe issue was in mdt_intent_lock_replace() where ACTIVE_WRITER\nlocks were not properly configured for client-server\ncommunication:\n\n1. l_conn_export was NULL, preventing cancellation RPCs from\n   being sent to the server\n2. LDLM_FL_LOCAL_ONLY flag was not being removed, causing\n   client-side local cancellation instead of server RPCs\n\nThis fix ensures that when ACTIVE_WRITER locks are sent to\nthe client, they have the proper export connection and flags\nfor distributed cancellation, allowing the server-side active\nwriter count to be properly decremented when locks are\ncancelled.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I5a4815478b7895b22f1a15e82b65f143ba303b0c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
